The Nigerian man was arrested when police raided his home last month where 26 young women were found on the premises. JOHANNESBURG A 42-year-old man accused of running a brothel in the North West has withdrawn his bail application without explanation.The Nigerian man was arrested when police raided his home last month.Twenty-six young women were found on the premises, the youngest only 14-years-old. The Hawks s Tlangelani Rikhotso says, Half-way through the court [proceedings] the accused decided to withdraw the application. The case was then postponed to 20 February 2017. 